Araucaria angustifolia

   [3318.jpg]
    Authority   (Bertol.) Kuntze
      Family    Pinopsida:Araucariaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3318

   Notes
   SOURCES (A. angustifolia (Bert.) O. Kuntze)
   Webb D 1984 pp 107 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 445 [USE]
   INSPIRE species 24 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, LIG, KTMP, USE]
   FAO For. Paper 77 pp 69
   KILLING T
   Frost resistant.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Evergreen tree.
   COMMON NAMES
   Parana pine, Parana wood, Brazilian pine, Pinho brasileiro, Pinho do
   parana, Pinheiro brasileiro, Pinheiro das missoes, Curiuva, Curi,
   Araucaria-pinho, Pino Brasil, Pino de missiones, Pino parana.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonym: A. brasiliana. Found at altitudes between 200-2200
   m, but only extends to latitudes lower than 500 m where cool air flows
   from the highlands towards the valleys. Occurs naturally in South
   America, between latitudes 19째30'-31째30'S and longitudes
   41째30'-54째30'W. It can reach a height of 25-40 m. The tree is drought
   hardy. Optimum annual wood production is 10-23 m3/ha.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
